ausible.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_004\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Clarify why 7 steps are claimed when only 5 reactions are listed\", \"Specify how spark-produced HCN reaches the formamide-rich environment\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.75,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.92,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.90,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.92\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.85,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.90,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.92,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.90,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.89,\n      \"feedback\": \"The most complete pathway with clear H\u2192S\u2192B environmental flow. Combines hydrothermal CO2 fixation with the bisulfite-protection strategy from Ritson & Sutherland 2018. Each environmental transition is justified: hydrothermal vents provide reduced C1 feedstocks, surface photochemistry/evaporite cycles enable formose and bisulfite-Strecker chemistry, and mild aqueous conditions allow hydrolysis. This pathway addresses the glycolaldehyde stability problem through bisulfite protection and provides complete feedstock-to-target connectivity.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"rxn_002 formate-to-formaldehyde reduction remains the weakest link; consider invoking serpentinization-derived H2 to improve thermodynamic drive\", \"Specify borate or other mineral catalyst for rxn_003\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n  \"overall_confidence\": 0.88,\n  \"network_feedback\": \"This is an exceptionally well-designed synthesis network for prebiotic serine production. The network demonstrates strong alignment with the peer-reviewed literature, incorporating all major experimentally grounded routes: the Ritson & Sutherland UV cyanometallate photoredox system (2012), the bisulfit